.description
Rayshade is a ray tracing program ported to the Amiga from UNIX.
Rayshade's features include eleven types of primitives, composite objects;
several types of light sources, texturing, bump mapping, antialiasing,
linear transformations, rendering of stereo pairs, rudimentary animation
support, and more.  Includes some example input files, original sources in
C, and diffs for the Amiga.  Amiga Release 0.5, an update to version 4.0PL6
Amiga Release 0.4 on disk 679.  
